FIGURE 4
. 

Neogyptis nonatoi

new species
. 
A
. Paratype MZUSP385, anterior region in dorsal view, pharynx everted, lateral antennae and tentacular cirri lost; 
B
. Holotype MZUSP386, anterior region, median antenna lost; 
C
. Same, parapodium 6; 
D
. Same, acicular notochaeta, striated, distally blunt; 
E
. Capillary notochaeta, long, striated, marginally serrated; 
F
. Median capillary notochaeta, with spirally arranged denticles; 
G
. Notochaeta short, curved distally and with serrated coarsely face; 
H
. Simple neurochaeta, distally blunt, marginally serrulated from basal to median portion; 
I
. Heterogomph falciger with long blade, marginally serrulated and distally bidentate; 
J
. Heterogomph falciger with short to median blade, marginally smooth and distally bidentate; 
K
. Geniculate neurochaetae, distally pointed.
